BT /F2 18 Tf 54.00 769.89 Td (1. Executive Summary) Tj ET
54.00 740.39 487.28 0.75 re f
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 729.39 Td (The project implements an AI-powered clinical classification platform that supports three) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 715.22 Td (prediction tasks: anemia classification from blood test markers, diabetes status) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 701.04 Td (classification from health indicators, and leukemia classification from microscopic blood) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 686.87 Td (smear images.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 664.69 Td (The anemia and diabetes modules use tabular machine learning pipelines. The leukemia) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 650.52 Td (module uses deep learning image models, including a blood-smear validator,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 636.34 Td (EfficientNet-B5, EfficientNet-B4, test-time augmentation, probability ensembling, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 622.17 Td (Grad-CAM visual explanations.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 599.99 Td (The main contribution is the integration of separate clinical prediction tasks into one) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 585.82 Td (local browser-based workflow. A user can select a disease model, enter values manually,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 571.64 Td (upload CSV files, extract CBC markers from report images, or analyze blood smear images) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 557.47 Td (with visual model focus maps.) Tj ET
BT /F2 18 Tf 54.00 517.29 Td (2. Clinical Problem and Motivation) Tj ET
54.00 487.79 487.28 0.75 re f
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 476.79 Td (Clinical classification is a recurring healthcare task. Physicians interpret laboratory) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 462.62 Td (markers, patient indicators, or medical images to decide whether a patient is healthy, at) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 448.44 Td (risk, or affected by a disease. Manual interpretation can be slow, inconsistent, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 434.27 Td (sensitive to missing data.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54.00 402.09 Td (2.1 Anemia) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 379.84 Td (Anemia may be related to iron deficiency, folate deficiency, vitamin B12 deficiency, or) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 365.67 Td (hemoglobin abnormalities. Complete blood count features and nutritional biomarkers contain) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 351.49 Td (useful signals, but combining them consistently is difficult in manual workflows.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54.00 319.32 Td (2.2 Diabetes) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 297.07 Td (Diabetes and prediabetes are associated with demographic, lifestyle, and health) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 282.89 Td (indicators. Early screening can help reduce complications, but health-indicator datasets) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 268.72 Td (contain many variables and imbalanced classes.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54.00 236.54 Td (2.3 Leukemia) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 214.29 Td (Leukemia detection from microscopic blood images requires specialist visual inspection of) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 200.12 Td (cell morphology. Automated image analysis can support screening and triage, especially) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 185.94 Td (when it also explains which image regions influenced the decision.) Tj ET
BT /F2 18 Tf 54.00 145.77 Td (3. Traditional and Older Approaches) Tj ET
54.00 116.27 487.28 0.75 re f
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 105.27 Td (Older approaches include manual threshold rules, spreadsheet comparison, isolated) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 91.09 Td (laboratory reports, and direct microscopy by specialists. These methods remain clinically) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54.00 76.92 Td (important but have limitations when many features interact or when large volumes of cases) Tj ET
endstream
